                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This May Be the Only Android Widget Pack You Ever Need to Buy]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-may-be-the-only-android-widget-pack-you-ever-need-to-buy/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/smartphones_displaying_customizable_widgets_with_several_widget_designs_in_the_background.png" length="688" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Play Store]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Struggling to find widgets? Look no further. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I have a love-hate relationship with widgets, but I recently stumbled across a set of widgets that scratched just about every itch. These widgets aren't free, but if you’ve never considered buying widgets before, this pack may just change your mind.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 16:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-may-be-the-only-android-widget-pack-you-ever-need-to-buy/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[10 Unusual Ways to Use a Portable Monitor]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/10-unusual-ways-to-use-a-portable-monitor/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/52665526919_fd65faf6c3_o.jpg" length="339160" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Monitors]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile Accessories]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't throw away that monitor, there's a lot you can do with it.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Portable monitors have traditionally been seen as simple extensions of a computer or laptop screen. This gives a bit more real estate for productivity or an improved gaming experience on the go. However, you shouldn’t pigeonhole them into these uses; there are plenty of ways to utilize your extra monitor.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 15:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/10-unusual-ways-to-use-a-portable-monitor/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Case Turns Your Mac Mini Into a Power Mac G4 Cube]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-case-turns-your-mac-mini-into-a-power-mac-g4-cube/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/m4-cubed.jpg" length="206" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Mac Mini (M4)]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The Cube is back.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Power Mac G4 Cube is one of Apple’s most iconic computer designs, even if it wasn’t actually a good computer. Now, a team in Australia is bringing that look and feel to Apple’s latest M4 Mac Mini.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 15:20:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-case-turns-your-mac-mini-into-a-power-mac-g4-cube/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Samsung Galaxy One UI 8 Update Officially Begins]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/samsung-galaxy-one-ui-8-android-16-update-officially-begins/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/three-samsung-phones-side-by-side-with-one-ui-the-one-ui-logo-next-to-them-and-the-samsung-and-android-logos-in-the-background.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy S25]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's starting with the Galaxy S25, but we have bad news for older phones. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Have you been patiently waiting for the big Samsung Galaxy Android 16 (One UI 8) update to start rolling out? If so, we have good news. This weekend, we learned that Samsung is ready to make it official and announced that the company is rolling out the first Galaxy One UI 8 update today, with more coming soon.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 15:08:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/samsung-galaxy-one-ui-8-android-16-update-officially-begins/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[A Step-by-Step Guide to Using SUMIFS in Microsoft Excel]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-excel-sumifs-function/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tony Phillips]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/microsoft-excel-illustration-highlighting-the-sumifs-function-with-the-excel-logo.png" length="428" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft Excel]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft 365]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft Office]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Calculate the sum of a range based on multiple criteria.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Microsoft Excel's SUMIFS function calculates the sum of values in a range of cells based on multiple conditions. It avoids the need for complex filtering, and its conditions can be numbers, text, or dates, making it great for dynamic data analysis.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 15:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/microsoft-excel-sumifs-function/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Apple TV+ Movies You Should Stream This Week (September 15 - 21)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-tv-plus-movies-stream-this-week-september-15/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Derek Malcolm]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/apple-tv-logo-centered-with-curved-film-strips-surrounding-it.png" length="700" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple TV+]]></category><category><![CDATA[Week]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            On tap are some excellent Apple TV+ movies for your work week.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you're like me and enjoy staying in on weekday evenings with a good movie, then I have five suggestions for some great films on <a href="https://shop-links.co/link/?exclusive=1&publisher_slug=howtogeek&u1=UUhtgUeUpU2016489&article_name=5+Apple+TV%2B+Movies+You+Should+Stream+This+Week+%28September+15+-+21%29&article_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fapple-tv-plus-movies-stream-this-week-september-15%2F&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftv.apple.com%2F" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Apple TV+</a> I've watched recently that I think you'll like, too.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 14:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-tv-plus-movies-stream-this-week-september-15/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Spotify Is Upgrading Free Accounts With New Features]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/spotify-is-upgrading-free-accounts-with-new-features/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/spotify.jpg" length="63" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Spotify]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You decide what you listen to now.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Spotify has removed a lot of restrictions that made its free tier a lot less appealing than YouTube Music. Now, ad-supported users don't have to rely on the old shuffle-only model. This update is rolling out globally and is the first major upgrade to the free tier in seven years.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 14:25:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/spotify-is-upgrading-free-accounts-with-new-features/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Simple Trick Gave My Pixel 10 a 3GB RAM Boost]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-simple-trick-gave-my-pixel-10-a-3gb-ram-boost/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/close-up-of-a-hand-holding-a-google-pixel-with-a-green-upward-arrow-and-symbols.png" length="1803" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel 10]]></category><category><![CDATA[ai]]></category><category><![CDATA[RAM]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Gemini]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Not all 12 GB RAM on Pixel is usable for regular tasks.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Google Pixel 10 comes with 12GB of RAM, but there’s a catch—only 9GB is available for your everyday tasks. Now, what if I told you there’s a way to unlock that extra 3GB and put it to work for regular use? Here’s everything you need to know about the Google Pixel 10’s RAM quirks.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 14:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-simple-trick-gave-my-pixel-10-a-3gb-ram-boost/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[These Google Pixel Phones Will Not Get Android 16]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/these-google-pixel-phones-will-not-get-android-16/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/person-holding-the-google-pixel-9-pro.jpg" length="72" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Some Google Pixel phones won't be getting the next update.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>With Android 16 dropping, it's an exciting time for a lot of Google Pixel users, bringing in new things like the cool Material 3 Expressive design, stronger security, and better productivity tools. However, if you've got an older Pixel, you might be out of luck, as a bunch of those devices won't be getting the latest operating system update.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 13:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/these-google-pixel-phones-will-not-get-android-16/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Movies on Prime Video to Watch This Week (September 15 - 21)]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/prime-video-movies-stream-this-week-september-15/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Chris Snellgrove]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/prime-video-logo-and-a-popcorn-bucket-next-to-it.png" length="3387" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Week]]></category><description><![CDATA[
